The paper proposes an algorithm for robot imitation learning, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm involves learning a joint probability density function and hidden semi-Markov models, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of virtual landmarks and object descriptions, which suggests a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the algorithm involves tracking and adapting to environmental changes, which is a common problem in control systems (cs.SY).
